FEMALE (
allotype
). Colour in alcohol (slightly darker in life) as in male but slightly darker; no dark colour pattern on opisthosoma.

Spermathecae quite narrow; all receptacles with distinct stalks and pyriform heads; median receptacles much longer than lateral ones, their stalks thin and slightly twisted, with sclerotized walls; lateral receptacles with voluminous heads and short stalks, their walls not sclerotised (
Fig. 9A
).
